1213
00:43:43,087 --> 00:43:45,289
He said he liked kimchi
and other Korean food,

1214
00:43:45,356 --> 00:43:46,991
so I prepared it like a fusion dish.

1215
00:43:47,057 --> 00:43:48,459
I wonder what it's like.

1216
00:43:48,525 --> 00:43:51,161
A BIG BITE

1217
00:43:53,530 --> 00:43:54,531
MMM

1218
00:43:55,666 --> 00:43:58,702
It was a little bland
when I had just the rice.

1219
00:43:58,769 --> 00:44:00,337
I wonder how it's seasoned.

1220
00:44:00,404 --> 00:44:02,039
-One more bite.
-The first dish was strong,

1221
00:44:02,106 --> 00:44:05,542
-so it may seem a bit bland in comparison.
-That may be the case.

1222
00:44:05,609 --> 00:44:06,477
That was his trick.

1223
00:44:06,543 --> 00:44:08,379
-It was the old boy.
-He knew it.

1224
00:44:08,445 --> 00:44:10,748
-Is this from experience?
-The old boy?

1225
00:44:10,814 --> 00:44:12,750
It tastes very healthy.

1226
00:44:13,217 --> 00:44:14,518
IF IT TASTES HEALTHY…

1227
00:44:14,585 --> 00:44:17,121
-Most low-sodium dishes are healthy.
-Right.

1228
00:44:17,187 --> 00:44:18,022
Me!

1229
00:44:18,088 --> 00:44:20,224
HEALTHY TASTE, MOST LOW-SODIUM DISHES, ME?

1230
00:44:20,290 --> 00:44:22,626
Isn't that the next mission?

1231
00:44:22,693 --> 00:44:24,561
-It's the next one.
-The next round.

1232
00:44:24,628 --> 00:44:26,830
-He wasn't looking for that now.
-He wasn't.

1233
00:44:26,897 --> 00:44:28,832
Did he misbubble his question
with the previous one?

1234
00:44:28,899 --> 00:44:30,634
-No, with the next one.
-People misbubble

1235
00:44:30,701 --> 00:44:33,404
-the answers and miss it by one.
-You're right.

1236
00:44:33,470 --> 00:44:35,272
Are you in the wrong lecture hall?

1237
00:44:35,339 --> 00:44:37,241
I thought I had to cook
a healthy dish without fire.

1238
00:44:38,175 --> 00:44:39,977
Should he have gone in the next round?

1239
00:44:41,512 --> 00:44:43,614
It's the kind of flavor I love.

1240
00:44:43,681 --> 00:44:46,483
It tastes very healthy and delicious.

1241
00:44:46,550 --> 00:44:49,486
At first, it smells mostly like thistle,

1242
00:44:49,553 --> 00:44:52,656
but toward the end,
seaweed comes in and backs it up.

1243
00:44:53,490 --> 00:44:55,292
-The seaweed oil. It does.
-Does it taste like seaweed?

1244
00:44:55,359 --> 00:44:56,827
There's depth to this dish.

1245
00:44:56,894 --> 00:44:58,629
There's depth.

1246
00:44:58,696 --> 00:44:59,830
Depth in the rice.

1247
00:44:59,897 --> 00:45:02,232
About how many meters?

1248
00:45:03,467 --> 00:45:05,436
-Is it deep?
-How many meters in the water?

1249
00:45:05,502 --> 00:45:07,271
-It's quite deep.
-Is it?

1250
00:45:07,337 --> 00:45:08,505
-Like 95 m deep.
-I mean it.

1251
00:45:08,572 --> 00:45:11,408
Chef Hyun-suk previously called him
a junior chef without any depth.

1252
00:45:11,475 --> 00:45:14,611
But Professor Yoo confirmed
that his dish has depth.

1253
00:45:14,678 --> 00:45:15,512
-It does.
-It's very deep.

1254
00:45:15,579 --> 00:45:19,049
It's organic, healthy, and delicious.

1255
00:45:19,116 --> 00:45:21,418
Then Min-jung, please try some.

1256
00:45:21,485 --> 00:45:23,587
That's Chef Hyun-suk's lasagna.

1257
00:45:23,654 --> 00:45:24,788
I've been dying to try the pasta.

1258
00:45:24,855 --> 00:45:25,689
THE PASTA SHE WANTED TO TRY

1259
00:45:27,391 --> 00:45:28,225
MMM

1260
00:45:29,359 --> 00:45:30,627
ISN'T IT GOOD?

1261
00:45:31,562 --> 00:45:33,130
This is made to my taste.

1262
00:45:34,398 --> 00:45:36,400
-I see.
-It must be something Min-jung likes.

1263
00:45:36,467 --> 00:45:37,868
It's so impressive.

1264
00:45:37,935 --> 00:45:38,936
It's cooked to perfection.

1265
00:45:39,002 --> 00:45:41,538
She says it's cooked to perfection.

1266
00:45:41,605 --> 00:45:43,440
-May I…
-He made it without fire.

1267
00:45:43,507 --> 00:45:46,543
-…take this home?
-She wants to take that home.

1268
00:45:46,610 --> 00:45:48,078
PLEASE PACK IT TO-GO

1269
00:45:48,145 --> 00:45:50,881
-I'm sorry, but…
-Hyun-suk should've competed last time.

1270
00:45:50,948 --> 00:45:52,583
Next, Chef Sung-jun's dish.

1271
00:45:52,649 --> 00:45:54,852
-He said it tasted healthy.
-A healthy flavor.

1272
00:45:54,918 --> 00:45:56,453
THE HUGE EYES ARE BACK

1273
00:45:56,520 --> 00:45:58,021
It tastes different, doesn't it?

1274
00:45:58,088 --> 00:46:00,557
-Does she like this better?
-Her eyes are huge.

1275
00:46:00,624 --> 00:46:02,426
-It's so good.
-It is.

1276
00:46:03,160 --> 00:46:04,361
It has depth,

1277
00:46:04,428 --> 00:46:08,298
and it tastes like he brought
fresh seafood from the deep sea.

1278
00:46:08,365 --> 00:46:09,700
-Really?
-Really.

1279
00:46:09,767 --> 00:46:11,568
It doesn't taste healthy.
It's downright good.

1280
00:46:11,635 --> 00:46:13,570
-Is it just good?
-Yes.

1281
00:46:13,637 --> 00:46:15,539
It tastes like a nice seafood risotto,

1282
00:46:15,606 --> 00:46:17,674
so I can't just say it tastes healthy.

1283
00:46:17,741 --> 00:46:19,376
-Is it seasoned well?
-Yes.

1284
00:46:19,443 --> 00:46:21,011
I guess he wasn't just
trying to be encouraging.

1285
00:46:21,078 --> 00:46:22,379
-He meant it.
-I did.

1286
00:46:22,446 --> 00:46:23,981
It's great if it's healthy too.

1287
00:46:24,047 --> 00:46:25,916
-It must be hard.
-It just became tough.

1288
00:46:25,983 --> 00:46:27,651
Yes, it's very hard to choose.

1289
00:46:27,718 --> 00:46:30,287
You must make a decision now.

1290
00:46:30,354 --> 00:46:32,623
You can give only one A plus per semester.

1291
00:46:32,689 --> 00:46:34,691
The mature student, Choi Hyun-suk.

1292
00:46:34,758 --> 00:46:36,560
The freshman, Kwon Sung-jun.

1293
00:46:36,627 --> 00:46:39,363
Which one of them gets the A plus?

1294
00:46:39,429 --> 00:46:40,798
<i>Press one for Sung-jun</i>

1295
00:46:41,865 --> 00:46:43,200
<i>and two for Hyun-suk.</i>

1296
00:46:44,368 --> 00:46:45,502
Press the button!

1297
00:46:46,370 --> 00:46:49,139
He pressed it. He made the tough decision.

1298
00:46:49,206 --> 00:46:54,278
Which one of them received
the highest grade from the professor?

1299
00:46:54,344 --> 00:46:56,046
Let's find out the result.

1300
00:46:56,613 --> 00:46:59,650
-Cook Without Using Fire.
-Cook Without Using Fire.

1301
00:46:59,716 --> 00:47:01,952
-Is it Hyun-suk, the mature student?
-It's too hard.

1302
00:47:02,019 --> 00:47:04,188
-It was too hard.
-Or is it Sung-jun, the freshman?

1303
00:47:04,254 --> 00:47:06,723
Who will get the A plus?

1304
00:47:06,790 --> 00:47:08,058
Who is it?

1305
00:47:08,125 --> 00:47:09,760
Professor Yoo's choice!

1306
00:47:09,827 --> 00:47:10,761
The assignment was hard.

1307
00:47:10,828 --> 00:47:13,263
Who received the highest grade?

1308
00:47:13,330 --> 00:47:15,532
Who's the winner?

1309
00:47:15,599 --> 00:47:17,267
CHOI HYUN-SUK WINS

1310
00:47:17,334 --> 00:47:18,635
WHO CAN COOK WITHOUT FIRE? I-SAGNA WINS

1311
00:47:18,702 --> 00:47:19,736
Choi Hyun-suk!

1312
00:47:19,803 --> 00:47:21,104
Lasagna.

1313
00:47:21,171 --> 00:47:23,140
Lasagna!

1314
00:47:23,207 --> 00:47:24,575
That's Hyun-suk and his experience.

1315
00:47:25,142 --> 00:47:28,679
Hyun-suk's one fine spring day
shall continue.

1316
00:47:31,415 --> 00:47:34,785
STARTS OFF THE YEAR WITH A WIN

1317
00:47:34,852 --> 00:47:36,787
This was such a wonderful dish

1318
00:47:36,854 --> 00:47:37,988
that came with depth,

1319
00:47:38,055 --> 00:47:39,756
-and it was so good.
-They both were.

1320
00:47:39,823 --> 00:47:42,292
How can I put this?
His dish tasted more on point.

1321
00:47:42,359 --> 00:47:44,761
The lasagna was more precise.

1322
00:47:44,828 --> 00:47:45,762
I'll repeat the class.

1323
00:47:45,829 --> 00:47:48,899
The chef with an on-point flavor,
Chef Hyun-suk gets the star!

1324
00:47:48,966 --> 00:47:50,167
-Congratulations.
-Congratulations.

1325
00:47:50,767 --> 00:47:52,603
Professor Yoo decided to choose

1326
00:47:52,669 --> 00:47:54,438
-Chef Choi Hyun-suk.
-Thank you.

1327
00:47:54,504 --> 00:47:56,440
He takes the first star of the year.

1328
00:47:56,506 --> 00:47:59,476
-That and a bottle of the finest whiskey.
-Thank you.

1329
00:47:59,543 --> 00:48:03,013
-It's an honor.
-Our best chef stays strong even in 2026!

1330
00:48:03,080 --> 00:48:04,882
Congratulations!

1331
00:48:05,382 --> 00:48:06,950
Thank you.

1332
00:48:07,017 --> 00:48:11,521
<i>We're about to begin the second cook-off</i>
<i>with ingredients from Ji-tae's fridge.</i>

1333
00:48:11,588 --> 00:48:15,459
The original Cooking Maniac,
Chef Yoon Nam-no,

1334
00:48:15,525 --> 00:48:17,728
<i>is up against Park Eun-yeong,</i>

1335
00:48:17,794 --> 00:48:21,331
who forfeited her goddess status
and became Successful Maniac.

1336
00:48:21,398 --> 00:48:23,600
Recently, many people are saying

1337
00:48:23,667 --> 00:48:27,137
-Chef Nam-no's madness was fake,
-I see.

1338
00:48:27,204 --> 00:48:29,539
that Chef Eun-yeong is the truly mad one.

1339
00:48:29,606 --> 00:48:30,641
He's just a pure guy.

1340
00:48:30,707 --> 00:48:33,076
-And kind-hearted.
-Yes, he's kind.

1341
00:48:33,143 --> 00:48:34,044
And good at recycling.

1342
00:48:34,111 --> 00:48:35,012
Recycling?

1343
00:48:35,078 --> 00:48:38,015
He always recycles well. A stand-up guy.

1344
00:48:38,081 --> 00:48:40,717
On the other hand,
Chef Eun-yeong looks like a goddess,

1345
00:48:40,784 --> 00:48:42,753
-She's scary.
-but your behaviors…

1346
00:48:42,819 --> 00:48:44,388
-The real deal.
-She's a tough cookie.

1347
00:48:44,454 --> 00:48:46,957
I don't think it's true,

1348
00:48:47,024 --> 00:48:49,826
and I don't know what people see in me
to say something like that.

1349
00:48:49,893 --> 00:48:51,628
She's the real deal
because she doesn't know.

1350
00:48:53,096 --> 00:48:55,866
She's recently at the top of her game.

1351
00:48:55,933 --> 00:48:58,101
<i>During the 2025 Championship,</i>

1352
00:48:58,168 --> 00:49:00,370
<i>she started with the first round,</i>

1353
00:49:00,437 --> 00:49:02,973
defeated everyone,
and moved on to the finals.

1354
00:49:03,040 --> 00:49:05,542
She's been on a crazy roll.

1355
00:49:05,609 --> 00:49:09,513
But Chef Nam-no said something like this.

1356
00:49:09,579 --> 00:49:11,682
"I don't care
if it's Eun-yeong or Sung-jun."

1357
00:49:11,748 --> 00:49:14,584
"The young'uns are all my prey."

1358
00:49:14,651 --> 00:49:15,953
-You don't care?
-You preyed on us a lot.

1359
00:49:16,019 --> 00:49:17,688
So you're the best of the young'uns?

1360
00:49:17,754 --> 00:49:19,723
You're right. In the previous season,

1361
00:49:19,790 --> 00:49:22,326
-I've never lost against Eun-yeong.
-You haven't.

1362
00:49:22,392 --> 00:49:25,362
And I've won all four times
against Sung-jun.

1363
00:49:25,429 --> 00:49:26,863
-Is that so?
-I won every time.

1364
00:49:26,930 --> 00:49:28,899
-He's right.
-It's true.

1365
00:49:28,966 --> 00:49:31,335
But the assignment tells me that

1366
00:49:31,401 --> 00:49:33,503
this will be disadvantageous
for Chef Nam-no.

1367
00:49:33,570 --> 00:49:35,472
I've never seen him eat healthy before.

1368
00:49:36,273 --> 00:49:38,875
Yes, you're right.
Why did he choose this round?

1369
00:49:38,942 --> 00:49:40,711
I may not be close with healthy food,

1370
00:49:40,777 --> 00:49:43,714
-but next to it is convenience food.
-It was convenience food.

1371
00:49:43,780 --> 00:49:45,215
The convenience food.

1372
00:49:45,282 --> 00:49:48,986
I know I've had much more convenient food
than any of you in here.

1373
00:49:50,420 --> 00:49:52,956
I think he misunderstood the assignment.

1374
00:49:53,023 --> 00:49:54,925
I'll pay more attention today

1375
00:49:54,992 --> 00:49:57,894
and make
at least one healthy meal for him.

1376
00:49:57,961 --> 00:49:59,396
-Thank you.
-I see.

1377
00:49:59,463 --> 00:50:01,264
Do you even eat convenience food?

1378
00:50:01,331 --> 00:50:02,466
Do you eat healthy food?

1379
00:50:02,532 --> 00:50:03,667
SO IMMATURE

1380
00:50:05,002 --> 00:50:07,004
CHEF NAM-NO'S INGREDIENTS: CHICKEN BREAST,
HAMBURGER STEAK, DUMPLING

1381
00:50:07,070 --> 00:50:09,072
CRACKERS, TOFU NOODLES, CARROT JUICE,
SOY MILK, LEMON JUICE, PROTEIN POWDER

1382
00:50:09,139 --> 00:50:11,641
What are you making, Chef Nam-no?

1383
00:50:11,708 --> 00:50:13,377
The name of my dish is

1384
00:50:13,944 --> 00:50:15,712
A Plus Please, for Sabayon.

1385
00:50:15,779 --> 00:50:18,248
A Plus Please, for Sabayon.

1386
00:50:18,315 --> 00:50:20,250
-A Plus Please, for Sabayon.
-A Plus Please, for Sabayon.

1387
00:50:20,317 --> 00:50:22,586
-A Plus Please, for Sabayon. What's that?
-Sabayon.

1388
00:50:22,652 --> 00:50:25,288
I'm going to make something delicious

1389
00:50:25,355 --> 00:50:26,990
with his favorite, chicken breast.

1390
00:50:27,057 --> 00:50:29,826
I know you always relied
on the microwave to cook the chicken,

1391
00:50:29,893 --> 00:50:32,329
but it'll turn into something
delicious yet healthy.

1392
00:50:32,396 --> 00:50:34,331
I'll also make sabayon with carrot juice.

1393
00:50:34,398 --> 00:50:35,766
Sabayon with carrot juice?

1394
00:50:35,832 --> 00:50:39,503
-I'm going to make sabayon.
-I see. Hence, the title.

1395
00:50:39,569 --> 00:50:43,073
Carrots are full of vitamin A
and beta carotene,

1396
00:50:43,140 --> 00:50:47,044
which will make your eyes
and your body healthy.

1397
00:50:47,110 --> 00:50:49,613
So Professor, A Plus Please, for Sabayon.

1398
00:50:50,047 --> 00:50:51,681
HIS CUTESINESS RAISES THE EXPECTATION

1399
00:50:52,249 --> 00:50:53,583
I'll look forward to it.

1400
00:50:54,518 --> 00:50:56,520
CHEF EUN-YEONG'S INGREDIENTS:
FROZEN SEAFOOD MIX, DONGTAE-TANG MEAL KIT

1401
00:50:56,586 --> 00:50:58,588
TOFU NOODLES, FROZEN VEGETABLE MIX,
BROCCOLI POWDER

1402
00:50:58,655 --> 00:51:01,691
Up against him is Chef Eun-yeong.
What are you making?

1403
00:51:01,758 --> 00:51:03,493
My dish is called

1404
00:51:03,560 --> 00:51:04,895
Attack Yoon Nam-no.

1405
00:51:04,961 --> 00:51:07,197
-Attack Yoon Nam-no.
-Attack Yoon Nam-no.

1406
00:51:07,264 --> 00:51:08,331
You're attacking him outright?

1407
00:51:08,398 --> 00:51:10,634
-For no reason?
-It's not a dish name.

1408
00:51:10,700 --> 00:51:11,768
-How scary.
-All right.

1409
00:51:11,835 --> 00:51:13,837
-What will you make to attack him?
-She's crazy.

1410
00:51:13,904 --> 00:51:16,940
I'll make seafood balls and make soup.

1411
00:51:17,007 --> 00:51:20,410
It's winter, so I thought he could
warm his body with this hot soup.

1412
00:51:20,477 --> 00:51:23,914
Also, his freezer had the <i>dongtae-tang</i>
he didn't know what to do with.

1413
00:51:23,980 --> 00:51:26,349
I'll make the seafood balls
using the pollack in there.

1414
00:51:26,416 --> 00:51:29,453
So I'll take the problematic soup meal kit

1415
00:51:29,519 --> 00:51:31,054
and Chef Nam-no,

1416
00:51:31,121 --> 00:51:32,956
then throw them both away.

1417
00:51:34,925 --> 00:51:35,926
She's truly a maniac.

1418
00:51:35,992 --> 00:51:36,993
She'll get rid of Nam-no too.

1419
00:51:37,060 --> 00:51:38,929
WHO'LL WIN THE MANIAC MATCH?

1420
00:51:38,995 --> 00:51:42,099
And now, you'll begin
Professor Yoo's assignment,

1421
00:51:42,165 --> 00:51:46,103
Make a Healthy Dish.

1422
00:51:46,169 --> 00:51:50,173
He wishes to get an A plus
and become the show's scholarship student.

1423
00:51:50,240 --> 00:51:52,676
The fake maniac, Chef Yoon Nam-no.

1424
00:51:52,742 --> 00:51:56,079
But she tells Nam-no to wake up
and be ready for his academic probation.

1425
00:51:56,146 --> 00:52:00,250
The real maniac,
Chef Park Eun-yeong will fight him.

1426
00:52:00,317 --> 00:52:03,687
Which one of them will become
the top of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> class?

1427
00:52:03,753 --> 00:52:06,156
Let the 15-minute assignment begin!

1428
00:52:06,323 --> 00:52:07,457
SALUTE!

1429
00:52:08,191 --> 00:52:09,392
SABAYON MASTER, NAM-NO

1430
00:52:09,459 --> 00:52:11,261
It's yet another difficult assignment.

1431
00:52:11,328 --> 00:52:13,830
He's using lots of carrot juice.

1432
00:52:13,897 --> 00:52:15,799
What's sabayon usually made of?

1433
00:52:15,866 --> 00:52:18,101
White wine and eggs,

1434
00:52:18,168 --> 00:52:19,703
but recently, many people use veggies.

1435
00:52:19,769 --> 00:52:21,104
VEGGIE JUICE INSTEAD OF WINE

1436
00:52:21,171 --> 00:52:22,939
It's because many people don't drink.

1437
00:52:23,006 --> 00:52:25,275
He's substituting wine with carrot juice.

1438
00:52:25,342 --> 00:52:27,511
He's using that much butter
to make a healthy dish?

1439
00:52:27,577 --> 00:52:29,646
-That much butter?
-You must make a healthy dish.

1440
00:52:29,713 --> 00:52:31,948
It'll give you high cholesterol.

1441
00:52:32,015 --> 00:52:32,849
How is that healthy?

1442
00:52:32,916 --> 00:52:34,451
Butter is good for you.

1443
00:52:34,518 --> 00:52:36,453
It's a part of the ketogenic diet.

1444
00:52:36,520 --> 00:52:39,289
-The ketogenic diet?
-It's okay to take lots of butter.

1445
00:52:39,356 --> 00:52:40,590
Why are you drinking that?

1446
00:52:40,657 --> 00:52:41,958
-This is good.
-I see.

1447
00:52:42,025 --> 00:52:43,927
A healthy dish with convenience food.

1448
00:52:45,262 --> 00:52:48,965
Does health come first? Or is it taste?

1449
00:52:49,032 --> 00:52:51,668
Well, it'll have to be both,

1450
00:52:51,735 --> 00:52:55,105
but I don't think
two blocks of butter will help.

1451
00:52:55,172 --> 00:52:56,339
What will happen?

1452
00:52:56,406 --> 00:52:59,142
Chef Eun-yeong keeps her pace
and does business as usual.

1453
00:52:59,209 --> 00:53:00,944
TWO SHAPES FOR GREEN ONION!

1454
00:53:01,611 --> 00:53:03,413
SPEED, UP!

1455
00:53:04,047 --> 00:53:05,849
POWER, UP!

1456
00:53:06,016 --> 00:53:07,484
RHYTHMICAL!

1457
00:53:08,618 --> 00:53:09,986
FINISHES PREPPING VEGGIES!

1458
00:53:10,053 --> 00:53:12,756
Chef Eun-yeong preps the seafood balls.

1459
00:53:12,822 --> 00:53:13,657
FROZEN SEAFOOD MIX

1460
00:53:13,723 --> 00:53:18,028
She's making seafood balls right now.

1461
00:53:18,094 --> 00:53:22,065
